The paper discusses techniques for reducing the size of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning applications such as natural language processing and computer vision. This makes it likely that the paper would be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of pruning to reduce the number of parameters in the network, which is a common technique in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which further support these categories.
